headline: Why Dell (DELL) Shares Are Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of computer hardware and IT solutions company Dell (NYSE:DELL) fell 2.9% in the morning session after a broader tech sector sell-off was triggered by concerns about an AI bubble following financial results from industry bellwether Oracle.

headline: Dell Technologies (DELL) Is Up 5.2% After Record AI Server Orders And Dividend Hike - Has The Bull Case Changed?
summary: Dell Technologies recently reported record Q3 fiscal 2026 results, highlighting strong AI server momentum with US$12.30 billion in quarterly AI server orders and an increased annual dividend of US$2.10 per share following an 18% raise approved earlier this year. headline: The AI Trade Is Tanking as Anxieties Reemerge
summary: Oracle’s  latest earnings have stoked further anxiety around the artificial-intelligence trade.  The stock is down more than 16% in early trading Thursday, and is taking much of the AI data-center hardware trade with it.  Shares of  Nvidia Advanced Micro Devices Broadcom Dell Technologies  and  Hewlett Packard Enterprise  were all down at least 2%.
